<div class="container page-color">
  <div class="panel panel-default container-color col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3" style="margin-top: 20px">
      <h3 class="base-color">SMART TV ACCOUNT LINKING</h3>
      <h4>This app REQUIRES a raspberry pi running on your network already running the <a href="https://github.com/eclair4151/AlexaControlledSamsungTV">Custom Smart TV software.</a> Unfortunately this is required and if you do not have this setup this app will not work for you.
      <br><br>
      This login is for your Custom Smart TV account. This is NOT for your Amazon, Alexa, or Samsung account. To create an account click here: <a href="/create_account">Create Account </a>
      <br><br>
      To see a tutorial on how to set up your Raspberry Pi <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-uhd33FiEUM">Click Here</a>
      </h4>
    <form name="loginForm" action="/alexa_login" class="panel-body panel-container" method="post">
      <input type="hidden" name="state" value="<%= @state %>">
      <input type="hidden" name="redirect_uri" value="<%= @redirect_uri %>">

      <%= hidden_field_tag :authenticity_token, form_authenticity_token %>
      <div class="form-group" style="margin: 15px">
        <label for="usr">Email:</label>
        <input type="email" class="form-control" id="usr" name="email" required>
      </div>
      <div class="form-group" style="margin: 15px">
        <label for="pwd">Password:</label>
        <input type="password" class="form-control" id="pwd" name="password" required>
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default base-color" style="float:right; margin:15px;">LINK ACCOUNT</button>
      <p id="error"  style="color:red"><%= flash[:error] %></p>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
